as previous books have failed to examine to what extent these forms of resistance should be regarded as reactions to changing regimes of provision. Continuing the recently growing interest in the interdependence of countercultures and consumer society, the focus on violence gives the argument a unique twist, making the book thought-provoking and engaging"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on information from the publisher. 0aPolitical violencezGermany (West)xHistory. 0aProtest movementszGermany (West)xHistory. 0aRadicalismzGermany (West)xHistory. 0aGovernment, Resistance tozGermany (West)xHistory. 0aConsumption (Economics)xPolitical aspectszGermany (West)xHistory. 0aCapitalismxPolitical aspectszGermany (West)xHistory. 0aSocial changezGermany (West)xHistory. 0aGermany (West)xPolitics and government. 0aGermany (West)xSocial conditions. 0aGermany (West)xEconomic conditions. 4aElectronic books.2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)epublisher. 0aSocial history, popular culture, and politics in Germany40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.6713536